<H3> <TI>   Xinjiang Uygur Delegation Visits Malaysia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delegation Departs Malaysia </H4>
<F P=102> OW2401125794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1239 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2401125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, January 24 (XINHUA) -- Tomur Dawamat, 
vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's 
Congress of China left here for home today after a one-week 
goodwill visit to Malaysia. 
  During the visit, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad, 
speaker of the lower house of Parliament Mohamed Zahir, 
president of Senate G. Vadiveloo met with Tomur respectively and 
exchanged views on the further enhancement of bilateral 
relations, including economic and trade links. 
  Supreme Head of State Sultan Azlan Shah and his wife hosted 
a 
luncheon today for Tomur and his wife. 
  Tomur and his party toured Malaysia's national car plant in 
Shah Alam near here, the industrial zone of Penang and other 
economic institutions. 

</TEXT>

