<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Minister Deng Nan Meets Thai Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1801103394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0821 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1801103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, January 18 (XINHUA) -- Thai Prime Minister 
Chuan Likphai said here today that he hopes new progress and 
achievements would be scored in Thailand-China bilateral 
cooperation in the fields of science and technology, economy and 
trade. 
  The prime minister made the remarks when meeting with Deng 
Nan, vice minister of the Chinese State Science and Technology 
Commission this morning. 
  Deng said the ties between China and Thailand are at their 
best time, which has constituted a good foundation for closer 
bilateral cooperation in science and technology. 
  During meeting with Deng Monday [17 January], Thai Foreign 
Minister Prasong Sunsiri said that both Thailand and other ASEAN 
countries are willing to conduct further technological exchanges 
and cooperation with China. 
  Prasong expressed his hope that China, under the guidance of 
Deng Xiaoping's blueprint, will achieve even greater success in 
national construction. 
  Deng Nan is on a five-day good-will visit to Thailand at the 
invitation of the Department of Technical and Economic 
Cooperation under the Office of the Prime Minister. She is to 
leave for home on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

