<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Deficit With Japan Reaches $14.22 Billion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101102094 Taipei CNA in English 0812 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2101102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lilian Wu] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, Jan. 21 (CNA) -- Taiwan's trade deficit 
with Japan registered a record US$14.22 billion in 1993, up 10.5 
percent from the previous year, the Ministry of Economic Affairs 
said Friday [21 January]. 
  The ministry noted that Taiwan exported US$8.97 billion 
worth 
of goods and services to Japan in 1993, up 0.9 percent from the 
previous year, while imports increased 6.5 percent to US$23.19 
billion. 
  The ministry said imports from Japan accounted for 30.1 
percent of Taiwan's total imports last year, the same ratio as 
in 1992. Parts, components and machinery made up 90 percent of 
the imports. 

</TEXT>

