<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Ministry To Authorize More Bond Dealers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101183994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1053 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2101183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 11 Jan (XINHUA) -- The Ministry of Finance 
will expand at certain places the experiment concerning 
first-class government bond dealers. After submitting an 
application to and obtaining approval from the authorities, 
nonpolicy-nature banks, securities companies, trust and 
investment companies, and other nonbank monetary organizations 
may serve as first-class government bond dealers of the People's 
Republic of China, join the 1994 national group of contract 
dealers of government bonds, and directly sign a contract with 
the Ministry of Finance to deal in government bonds. 
  First-class government bond dealers, as an important medium 
of the government bond market, shoulder certain obligations in 
committing themselves to marketing government bonds and 
promoting the development of the government bond market. At the 
same time, they enjoy the right to and precedence in dealing 
with the central bank in the open government bond market. 
  A responsible person concerned at the Ministry of Finance 
has 
pointed out: To expand the experiment involving first-class 
government bond dealers at selected places is an important 
measure for reforming the government bond market. To promote 
the work actively and properly, the Ministry of Finance, working 
together with the People's Bank of China and the China 
Securities Supervision and Administration Committee, has 
formulated the "Procedures for Managing First-Class Government 
Bond Dealers of the People's Republic of China" and the 
"Procedures for Examining and Affirming First-Class Government 
Bond Dealers." They will jointly examine and approve the 
applications of first-class government bond dealers. Finance 
organizations may, as of today, submit their applications and 
their intention to deal in the first issuing of 1994 government 
bonds to the State Debts Administration of the Ministry of 
Finance. 

</TEXT>

