<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Receive Loans for Construction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1901162094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1526 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1901162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 19 (XINHUA) -- A financial group 
consisting of several major specialized banks in China will 
provide a 40 million U.S.-dollar unsecured loan for the basic 
construction of the capital city, according to a contract signed 
here today. 
  The five-year loan will be jointly provided by the 
Industrial 
and Commercial Bank of China, the Bank of China, the Everbright 
Bank of China, the Citic Industrial Bank, the Beijing branch of 
the Bank of Communications, the Everbright International Trust 
and Investment Corporation and Huaxia Bank. 
  The loan will be entrusted to the Investment Corporation for 
Economic Development of Beijing, which was established for 
funding the basic construction of Beijing. 

